---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import { url } from '../../lib/site';
---
<BaseLayout title="Review Policy">
  <Hero
    eyebrow="Resources · Review Policy"
    title="Review Policy"
    lead="How the ML4H review process works."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Review process overview</h2>
      <p>
        ML4H uses a double-blind review process: reviewers are unaware of author
        identities, and authors are unaware of reviewer identities during the
        review period.
      </p>

      <h3>Review stages</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Initial review.</strong> Each submission receives reviews from multiple program committee members.</li>
        <li><strong>Author response.</strong> Authors may submit a brief rebuttal addressing factual errors.</li>
        <li><strong>Discussion.</strong> Reviewers and area chairs discuss submissions before making final recommendations.</li>
        <li><strong>Final decision.</strong> Program chairs make accept/reject decisions informed by reviews and area chair recommendations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Reviewer assignments</h3>
      <p>
        Reviewers are assigned based on their stated expertise areas and declared
        conflicts of interest. Conflicts with authors at the same institution or
        recent collaborators are automatically excluded.
      </p>

      <h3>Desk rejection</h3>
      <p>
        Submissions may be desk-rejected without review if they are significantly
        out of scope, violate formatting requirements, or contain obvious ethical
        violations.
      </p>

      <div class="btn-row">
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href={url('resources/reviewing-guidelines')}>Reviewing Guidelines</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href={url('resources')}>Back to Resources</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
